A governorship aspirant in the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Kaduna State, Alhaji Sani Mohammad Sha’aban, has petitioned the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) over the party’s delegates congresses in the state.   Dagogo: Court order threatens Rivers governorship primary     Winners emerge in PDP House of Representatives primaries     Goje denies participating in PDP primary   He alleged that there were no congresses across the 23 local ?governments, contrary to a report by the party’s Appeal Committee that the delegates’ congresses were successful. The committee headed by Mrs. Tinuke Gbadejo Ogunrinde had last Saturday told reporters at the state secretariat of the party that congresses were held and they were hitch-free, as no petition was received before, during and after the congresses.